===== Involved rules descriptions:

[iamf][Rule #4] id: assert-audio-element-obu
Section 3.6
Audio Element OBU checks:
- audio_element_id SHALL be unique within an IA Sequence.
- num_substreams SHALL NOT be set to 0.
- When audio_element_type = 0 (CHANNEL_BASED), num_parameters SHALL be set to 0, 1, or 2.
- When audio_element_type = 1 (SCENE_BASED), num_parameters SHALL be set to 0.
- The type PARAMETER_DEFINITION_MIX_GAIN SHALL NOT be present in Audio Element OBU.
- The parameter type SHALL NOT be duplicated in one Audio Element OBU.
- When codec_id = fLaC or ipcm, the type PARAMETER_DEFINITION_RECON_GAIN SHALL NOT be present.
- When num_layers > 1, the type PARAMETER_DEFINITION_RECON_GAIN SHALL be present.
- When highest loudspeaker_layout does not correspond to Mono, Stereo, or 3.1.2 and num_layers > 1, both PARAMETER_DEFINITION_DEMIXING and PARAMETER_DEFINITION_RECON_GAIN SHALL be present.

[iamf][Rule #7] id: assert-scalable-channel-layout-generation
Section 3.6.3
Channel Layout Generation Rule checks:
- For scalable channel audio, channel layouts SHALL follow non-decreasing order of surround, LFE and height channels.
- Duplicate layers are NOT allowed.

[iamf][Rule #8] id: assert-scalable-channel-group-format
Section 3.6.3
Channel Group Format checks:
- For scalable channel audio, substream_count and coupled_substream_count SHALL match expected values derived from layout transitions.

[iamf][Rule #21] id: assert-profile-restrictions
Section 4.1
Simple Profile restrictions:
- There SHALL be only one unique Audio Element OBU.
- The IA parser, decoder, and processor SHALL be able to handle up to 16 channels.

[iamf][Rule #24] id: assert-descriptor-obus-order
Section 5.1.1
Descriptor OBUs SHALL be placed in the following order:
1. One IA Sequence Header OBU
2. All Codec Config OBUs
3. All Audio Element OBUs
4. All Mix Presentation OBUs
An IA Sequence is composed of a series of OBUs in the sequence of a set of Descriptors followed by their associated IA Data.

